docs.lead_paragraph: Week Ended Feb. 4, 1955 Softness of the British pound and a steady Undertone in the Canadian dollar represented the only changes of significance last week. In neither case, however, was the trend accompanied by any substantial turnover--on the contrary, turnover was light.

docs.snippet: The foreign exchange market was in the doldrums last week. The undertone was soft from its opening, resulting in a steady attrition of values. At least this applied to the British and Canadian remittances. On the Continent, the Netherlands guilder...
docs.lead_paragraph: The foreign exchange market was in the doldrums last week. The undertone was soft from its opening, resulting in a steady attrition of values. At least this applied to the British and Canadian remittances. On the Continent, the Netherlands guilder was weak, but others in that group were steady and little changed.
